    "base_path":  "/guidance/authorise-an-agent-for-certain-taxes-through-your-business-tax-account",
    "content_id":  "b0dd86fb-14e3-4daa-a82a-68b2bf8d4769",
    "description":  "Find out what to do if your agent asks you to authorise them through your business tax account.",
    "details":  {
                    "attachments":  [

                                    ],
                    "body":  "\u003cdiv class=\"govspeak\"\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"call-to-action\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eYou must not give your log in credentials to your agent or anyone else.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIf you’re an agent, you must not use your client’s credentials to log into any account. Find out \u003ca href=\"https://www.gov.uk/guidance/client-authorisation-an-overview\" class=\"govuk-link\"\u003ehow to register and get authorised as a tax agent to deal with HMRC.\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIf you’re a registered tax agent you can \u003ca href=\"https://www.gov.uk/guidance/change-or-remove-your-authorisations-as-a-tax-agent\" class=\"govuk-link\"\u003echange or remove your authorisations.\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eBefore an agent can deal with HMRC on your behalf you must first authorise them. How you authorise a tax agent is different depending on which tax they are dealing with.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eYou can authorise a tax agent through your business tax account for:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003ePAYE for employers\u003c/li\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003eConstruction Industry Scheme\u003c/li\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003eVAT\u003c/li\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003eVAT EU refunds\u003c/li\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003eVAT Mini One Stop Shop\u003c/li\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003eNotification of Vehicle Arrivals (NOVA)\u003c/li\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003eMachine Games Duty\u003c/li\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003eGambling Tax\u003c/li\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003eEmployment Related Securities\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eFor Self Assessment and Corporation Tax, talk to your agent about how they can get authorised.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eFor some taxes, your agent may ask you to authorise them using a link that they send to you — this is known as a digital handshake. Find out how you can \u003ca href=\"https://www.gov.uk/guidance/authorise-an-agent-to-deal-with-certain-tax-services-for-you\" class=\"govuk-link\"\u003eauthorise an agent using the digital handshake\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIf you are unsure, you should speak to your agent about the best method for authorising them.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"how-to-add-a-tax-agent-yourself-in-your-business-tax-account\"\u003eHow to add a tax agent yourself in your business tax account\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003col class=\"steps\"\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eGet an Agent Government Gateway Identifier from your agent.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSign in to your business tax account using your Government Gateway user ID and password.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSelect “Manage account”.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eOn the “Manage account” page, under the “Tax agents” category select “Add, view or change tax agents”.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSelect which tax you want to add a tax agent to.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eOn the “Manage who can access your taxes and schemes” page, select “Add an agent” for the tax that you would like to update.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eOn the “Add an agent to this tax or scheme?” page, enter the agent ID.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAfter entering the agent ID you will be asked to confirm that your agent’s details are correct — if they are select “Add agent”.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ol\u003e\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"if-you-need-remove-a-tax-agents-authorisation\"\u003eIf you need remove a tax agent’s authorisation\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIf you need to stop someone from dealing with HMRC on your behalf, you can remove their authorisation through your business tax account.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eFind out \u003ca href=\"https://www.gov.uk/guidance/change-or-remove-your-tax-agents-authorisation\" class=\"govuk-link\"\u003ehow to change or remove your tax agent’s authorisation\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e",
